00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:16.577
Even this point. Who are you?

00:35:16.577 --> 00:35:19.834
You see the subtleness, the&nbsp;
subtle point behind this.

00:35:19.834 --> 00:35:22.353
Can you see it? That’s what I told him.

00:35:22.353 --> 00:35:24.688
See Hanumana gets angry on this point.

00:35:24.688 --> 00:35:26.961
Hanumana, absolutely hundred percent.

00:35:26.961 --> 00:35:27.760
Who are you?&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:35:27.760 --> 00:35:28.581
Why should She love you?

00:35:28.581 --> 00:35:35.373
And because She loves us that’s why you&nbsp;
must accept what am I saying to you.

00:35:35.373 --> 00:35:40.560
What’s that?&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:43.840
Hello?

00:35:43.840 --> 00:35:47.786
Just open the door. Who else has come?

00:35:47.786 --> 00:35:50.174
[Sahaja Yogini talking]

00:35:50.174 --> 00:35:55.262
Hello your friend is coming is it? Who is coming?

00:35:55.263 --> 00:35:58.171
She is trying to talk to Me.

00:35:58.171 --> 00:36:04.298
She doesn’t like when I don’t&nbsp;
pay any attention to her.

00:36:04.298 --> 00:36:05.440
All right.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:08.160
Hello. How are you?

00:36:08.160 --> 00:36:13.334
It is nice to see you. Sit down. Sit down.

00:36:13.334 --> 00:36:17.120
So, how it becomes subtler&nbsp;
and subtler, one should see.

00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:19.520
And one should face it.

00:36:22.400 --> 00:36:51.680
And when the subtle ways, I must&nbsp;
say there is a difference between&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:36:51.680 --> 00:36:54.804
the senior Sahaja Yogis and this thing.

00:36:54.804 --> 00:36:56.663
You just see this. There is&nbsp;
a understanding, there is.

00:36:56.663 --> 00:36:58.694
Anything should be done from&nbsp;
the Sahaja Yoga point of view.

00:36:58.694 --> 00:36:59.865
Are we helping Sahaja Yoga or not.

00:36:59.865 --> 00:37:00.967
I think maturity comes with age.

00:37:00.967 --> 00:37:02.138
The concern should be Sahaja Yoga.

00:37:02.137 --> 00:37:03.962
And even if you, I mean I&nbsp;
said you must take up jobs.

00:37:03.962 --> 00:37:04.926
You must earn. Have to work.

00:37:04.926 --> 00:37:06.406
You have to improve your styles and things.

00:37:06.407 --> 00:37:07.440
Somewhat, but for Sahaja Yoga.

00:37:07.440 --> 00:37:09.200
It’s to be done for Sahaja Yoga.

00:37:09.200 --> 00:37:15.360
That’s not the aim. Aim is Sahaja Yoga.

00:37:15.360 --> 00:37:16.560
That’s the main point is.

00:37:18.080 --> 00:37:20.720
That Sahaja Yoga should be&nbsp;
placed as the highest thing

00:37:20.720 --> 00:37:29.093
and then only it will work out, because&nbsp;
all these subtle things will disappear.

00:37:29.093 --> 00:37:33.120
Otherwise these subtle things swallow&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:37:33.120 --> 00:37:33.130
you.

00:37:33.130 --> 00:37:33.428
And they come as [UNCLEAR], you see,&nbsp;
and they will give you ideas and things

00:37:33.428 --> 00:37:34.640
and it will start losing sight of it,

00:37:34.640 --> 00:37:38.480
because you must know that you have&nbsp;
been prophesized long time back.

00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:42.400
And you are doing such a tremendous work.

00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:47.200
It’s such a great work you are doing.

00:37:47.200 --> 00:37:50.960
I wish you could realize it, because&nbsp;
even that understanding is very subtle.

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:56.240
Then all other things you just throw away.

00:37:59.840 --> 00:38:06.880
That Sahaja Yoga itself is self-established&nbsp;
and have this self-esteem thing.

00:38:06.880 --> 00:38:08.160
It does not need from you.

00:38:08.720 --> 00:38:13.760
Only thing by taking it up yourself,&nbsp;
you improve in your status.

00:38:15.680 --> 00:38:17.840
Like that. Now see you understand.

00:38:18.400 --> 00:38:23.600
You’re doing no favor to Sahaja&nbsp;
Yoga or to Mataji Nirmala Devi.

00:38:23.600 --> 00:38:25.280
You’re doing favor to yourself.

00:38:25.280 --> 00:38:27.680
Now, this point is the point I tell you.

00:38:27.680 --> 00:38:31.840
All right? So you surrender.

00:38:31.840 --> 00:38:37.360
Surrendering is the only&nbsp;
way. There is no other way.

00:38:37.360 --> 00:38:39.680
And that’s why these problems can be solved now.

00:38:41.520 --> 00:38:45.840
So how do we do it?

00:38:45.840 --> 00:38:48.999
May God bless you.

00:38:48.999 --> 00:38:56.720
Oh, God! Good, good, come along, come along.

00:38:56.720 --> 00:39:00.317
How are you? Good.

00:39:00.317 --> 00:39:03.561
Who else is coming from Cambridge?

00:39:03.561 --> 00:39:06.805
Sahaja Yogi: I’m from Australia.

00:39:06.805 --> 00:39:11.290
Sahaja Yogi: [Unclear]. He stays in the ashram.

00:39:11.290 --> 00:39:13.580
Shri Mataji: Come along.

00:39:13.580 --> 00:39:18.160
John will be coming. Dalla [unsure] would come,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:39:18.160 --> 00:39:27.840
I’m sure.

00:39:27.840 --> 00:39:28.878
Sahaja Yogi: [Unclear].

00:39:28.878 --> 00:39:30.187
Shri Mataji: Not yet arrived.

00:39:30.188 --> 00:39:31.588
Sahaja Yogi: I know. [Unclear].

00:39:31.587 --> 00:39:33.040
Shri Mataji: Hmm. How to do it?

00:39:37.440 --> 00:39:38.122
“By not doing it”, he said, “by surrender”.

00:39:38.122 --> 00:39:48.400
Sahaja Yogi: I’ll miss Mother that; It&nbsp;
will then have a tendency to seat and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:51.520
there’ll be a big mess and there is&nbsp;
no point in doing anything, because-

00:39:51.520 --> 00:39:52.772
[Laughter]

00:39:52.772 --> 00:39:58.150
Shri Mataji: Then you do everything.&nbsp;
You see, when you become dynamic.

00:39:58.150 --> 00:40:02.800
If you are not becoming dynamic,&nbsp;
that means you are a gone case.

00:40:02.800 --> 00:40:10.928
This is the judgment point.

00:40:10.928 --> 00:40:13.963
Sahaja Yogi: We are all gone&nbsp;
cases here then, Mother.

00:40:13.963 --> 00:40:14.536
[Laughter]

00:40:14.536 --> 00:40:16.941
Shri Mataji: No. You can’t say that now.

00:40:16.941 --> 00:40:19.575
Sahaja Yogi: In fact, what we should be doing?

00:40:19.575 --> 00:40:21.866
Another Sahaja Yogi: Let it be as it is.

00:40:21.865 --> 00:40:24.499
Shri Mataji: You think so? I don’t think so.

00:40:24.500 --> 00:40:26.848
I’ve been praising you people all over.

00:40:26.848 --> 00:40:29.310
Of course, sometimes I used to get frantic.

00:40:29.310 --> 00:40:33.548
I must say the people in this country,&nbsp;
have only one problem, is lethargy.

00:40:33.548 --> 00:40:35.151
I will say, get active also.

00:40:35.151 --> 00:40:36.640
They can be only bathroom&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:40:36.640 --> 00:40:37.360
cleaners.

00:40:37.360 --> 00:40:38.240
This is the problem.

00:40:41.840 --> 00:40:45.440
So, the inactivity can be dangerous.

00:40:46.080 --> 00:40:48.160
But I’m saying of non-action.

00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:49.760
I’m not saying of inactivity,

00:40:50.560 --> 00:40:53.120
where the feeling that, “I’m&nbsp;
doing something” is not there.

00:40:58.240 --> 00:41:01.380
We have to be active, extremely active,&nbsp;
but say, “I’m not doing it “. Surrendered.

00:41:01.380 --> 00:41:01.634
If you are lethargic, then you are no good.

00:41:01.634 --> 00:41:01.983
I mean you are absolutely&nbsp;
wrong, ‘tamasik’, left-sided.

00:41:01.983 --> 00:41:02.880
Well, if you are active and you&nbsp;
know that, “It’s all surrendered,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:41:19.200 --> 00:41:22.960
I’m not doing it “.

00:41:22.960 --> 00:41:28.400
Then inactivity is not non-action.

00:41:28.400 --> 00:41:29.960
Non-action is very different.

00:41:29.960 --> 00:41:32.170
Like the sun comes and gives&nbsp;
you light. It just emits.

00:41:32.170 --> 00:41:44.320
It is non-action. It doesn’t say, “I’m doing it “.

00:41:44.320 --> 00:41:46.240
You see the difference between the two.

00:41:46.240 --> 00:41:47.840
It should be clearly understood.

00:41:47.840 --> 00:41:52.560
Sahaja Yogi: Do you think, Mother,&nbsp;
that sometimes there is a tendency&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:41:52.560 --> 00:41:58.320
to feel that if you do something&nbsp;
in an active way, that you may&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:41:59.120 --> 00:42:04.080
get a catch in the left or right heart. Then&nbsp;
there’s a sense, there is a tendency then&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:42:04.080 --> 00:42:10.000
not to do anything, since we go closer of your –&nbsp;
you that you might go catching or doing something.

00:42:10.000 --> 00:42:11.763
Another Sahaja Yogi: It’s hypochondriac thing.

00:42:11.763 --> 00:42:13.600
Sahaja Yogi: And that’s the hypochondria.

00:42:13.600 --> 00:42:17.573
Another Sahaja Yogi: I’m catching on left&nbsp;
heart, so I can’t do anything… the whole day.

00:42:17.573 --> 00:42:21.582
Shri Mataji: I mean, Sahaja&nbsp;
Yoga is not for such cowards.

00:42:21.582 --> 00:42:22.480
They are useless, they better get out.

00:42:23.280 --> 00:42:29.876
You see, it’s meant for people who are&nbsp;
real warriors, you see, we need soldiers.

00:42:29.876 --> 00:42:33.521
Sahaja Yogi : We must fight now.&nbsp;
We got to get out and fight.

00:42:33.521 --> 00:42:39.018
Shri Mataji: They will go out of circulation,&nbsp;
don’t you worry, all such people, very soon.

00:42:39.018 --> 00:42:42.901
So, those who are afraid of&nbsp;
catching, they go out of circulation.

00:42:42.901 --> 00:42:43.200
Here&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:42:43.200 --> 00:42:46.560
we are not here to look after your chakras.

00:42:48.640 --> 00:42:52.400
We are here to work for Sahaja Yoga.

00:42:55.120 --> 00:42:58.880
When you start working for Sahaja Yoga,&nbsp;
you are automatically cured and geared up.

00:42:59.680 --> 00:43:00.800
That’s what it is.

00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:05.120
Sahaja Yogi: Donna said something very&nbsp;
appropriate when we were talking. She said,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:43:05.120 --> 00:43:07.400
“One just has to look at the little ones.”

00:43:07.400 --> 00:43:11.840
Shri Mataji: Yes.

00:43:11.840 --> 00:43:15.599
She is working for all of&nbsp;
you left, right everywhere.

00:43:15.599 --> 00:43:17.372
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:43:17.372 --> 00:43:20.847
That’s a game. That’s a game she’s playing.

00:43:20.847 --> 00:43:24.038
The game we are all in like you, smiling too.

00:43:24.038 --> 00:43:24.960
Sahaja Yogi:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:43:24.960 --> 00:43:28.640
This is what we must realize&nbsp;
that they work very hard.

00:43:28.640 --> 00:43:32.720
Shri Mataji: That’s true!&nbsp;
Extremely, extremely hard.

00:43:33.760 --> 00:43:37.151
And they scream and shout and everything.

00:43:37.151 --> 00:43:40.960
Sahaja Yogi: Cause it is quite obvious that&nbsp;
when someone comes in, who’s got a bad catch,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:43:41.600 --> 00:43:48.540
because the working-out starts&nbsp;
immediately because of things.

00:43:48.540 --> 00:43:49.418
Shri Mataji: What things?

00:43:49.418 --> 00:43:53.840
Better you learn from them.

00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:57.036
I should be the one, who is catching the most.

00:43:57.036 --> 00:43:58.773
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:43:58.774 --> 00:44:00.094
Yes! What happened?

00:44:00.094 --> 00:44:01.831
Sahaja Yogi: Nothing bad.

00:44:01.831 --> 00:44:03.360
Shri Mataji: There we&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:03.360 --> 00:44:07.840
have.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:18.320 --> 00:44:21.840
Humm.

00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:30.995
Maybe that is, I don’t know. You see, it’s a&nbsp;
mathematics, which cannot be calculated easily.

00:44:30.994 --> 00:44:33.760
It’s the thing you go five&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:33.760 --> 00:44:34.635
steps forward, three steps backwards,

00:44:34.635 --> 00:44:35.840
eight steps forward, four steps backwards.

00:44:36.480 --> 00:44:38.880
Ten steps forward, eleven steps backwards.

00:44:38.880 --> 00:44:38.956
And where do you reach? What is the speed?

00:44:38.956 --> 00:44:39.001
That’s what England is.

00:44:39.001 --> 00:44:39.046
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:44:39.046 --> 00:44:39.122
But everybody of the whole is progressing.

00:44:39.121 --> 00:44:39.207
No doubt, slow and steady. We’ll win the race.

00:44:39.208 --> 00:44:39.385
Sahaja Yogi: I mean a wind of change came in the&nbsp;
last week when this girl arrived from Australia.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:39.384 --> 00:44:39.535
I mean it was really, someone I never met&nbsp;
so positive and everything else like that.

00:44:39.536 --> 00:44:39.644
Shri Mataji: They are the&nbsp;
children of convicts, you see? So.

00:44:39.644 --> 00:44:39.752
So fresh! Annick, there is&nbsp;
another one. Her name was Annick.

00:44:39.752 --> 00:44:39.857
She met us in Orleans. She&nbsp;
came all the way to meet Marie.

00:44:39.857 --> 00:44:39.891
Ah, you were there.

00:44:39.891 --> 00:44:39.963
She went round and took all the posters.

00:44:39.963 --> 00:44:40.051
You see Marie, as usual, brought up from England.

00:44:40.051 --> 00:44:40.184
So, she said, “Mother, she didn’t&nbsp;
tell me beforehand. She had put the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:40.185 --> 00:44:40.311
advertisement in the paper. But,&nbsp;
she didn’t find out when it was”.

00:44:40.311 --> 00:44:40.408
So, it was on the third day&nbsp;
the advertisement stopped.

00:44:40.408 --> 00:44:40.511
And there were no advertisements&nbsp;
for the two days before.

00:44:40.511 --> 00:44:40.592
So, this Annick said, “Doesn’t matter”.

00:44:40.592 --> 00:44:40.689
She went and put posters&nbsp;
everywhere eight days before.

00:44:40.689 --> 00:44:40.736
Everybody put the posters.

00:44:40.736 --> 00:44:40.813
And on the poster only, Annick got so many.

00:44:40.813 --> 00:44:40.928
And Marie said, “Mother, I’m&nbsp;
still an intuit, I don’ know.

00:44:40.929 --> 00:44:41.052
This thing happened; the third day&nbsp;
we got all a big [unclear] crowd.

00:44:41.051 --> 00:44:41.224
But these people who came with the posters, stayed&nbsp;
on for two days and really came up very well.

00:44:41.224 --> 00:44:41.292
And then, they started working it out.

00:44:41.293 --> 00:44:41.356
Now Paris is very well established.

00:44:41.356 --> 00:44:41.498
But this is what it is and the way she,&nbsp;
I mean, tremendous she was, isn’t it?

00:44:41.498 --> 00:44:41.599
Orleans, she did it very well.&nbsp;
She is really tremendous.

00:44:41.599 --> 00:44:41.680
To her, Sahaja Yoga is her life. Absolutely.

00:44:41.680 --> 00:44:44.400
Australians are going to show&nbsp;
a way to you people, I think.

00:44:44.960 --> 00:44:52.928
The convicts are born here to pull us&nbsp;
down everywhere, you go everywhere.

00:44:52.928 --> 00:44:54.808
You find those convicts, eh?

00:44:54.807 --> 00:44:55.680
Sahaja Yogi:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:44:55.680 --> 00:45:04.056
We need an exchange scheme.

00:45:04.056 --> 00:45:04.829
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:45:04.830 --> 00:45:06.508
Sahaja Yogi: We’ll send some&nbsp;
over there. No sense up here.

00:45:06.508 --> 00:45:06.700
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:45:06.700 --> 00:45:10.240
Shri Mataji: No, I think it is&nbsp;
alcoholism, of the worst time.

00:45:11.200 --> 00:45:16.960
Now in front of her house, we find&nbsp;
five, six of them permanently circle.

00:45:16.960 --> 00:45:18.080
One of them is a lady.

00:45:18.800 --> 00:45:21.680
Early in the morning, they are all drinking.

00:45:22.240 --> 00:45:27.360
And by yesterday we were, me and this&nbsp;
doctor who has come, we were going down.

00:45:27.360 --> 00:45:32.080
One of them was standing with a bottle and&nbsp;
was singing and going forward and backwards.

00:45:32.800 --> 00:45:35.200
So this Indian doctor got a fright.

00:45:35.200 --> 00:45:38.400
He said, “Better go by another road,&nbsp;
because he may just shoot off”.

00:45:38.400 --> 00:45:46.080
I said, “So this is what it is”.

00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:50.240
But Swiss people are very&nbsp;
speedy, very speedy people.

00:45:50.880 --> 00:45:52.880
They are on the other side. They are so speedy.

00:45:53.680 --> 00:45:57.680
Means, you know, it’s like a low&nbsp;
train which never reaches the point.

00:45:57.680 --> 00:46:00.560
And the fast one which always&nbsp;
misses the station, it is like that.

00:46:02.400 --> 00:46:03.840
I don’t know which one to travel.

00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:06.233
[Shri Mataji is laughing]

00:46:06.233 --> 00:46:08.435
Sahaja Yogi: [Unclear].

00:46:08.435 --> 00:46:09.680
Shri Mataji:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:46:09.680 --> 00:46:12.000
That is the situation of the West is.

00:46:12.000 --> 00:46:17.840
So, when you realize all this, we&nbsp;
must see and try to correct it.

00:46:17.840 --> 00:46:22.640
But only difference perhaps is that&nbsp;
difference- difference I find in this,

00:46:23.520 --> 00:46:25.708
that they understand their mistakes. And-

00:46:25.708 --> 00:46:28.960
Sahaja Yogi: It’s really the German&nbsp;
section, I think. They really.

00:46:28.960 --> 00:46:32.640
Shri Mataji: No, all of them. Swiss also.

00:46:32.640 --> 00:46:33.840
They also, they all understand.

00:46:33.840 --> 00:46:38.080
They say, “Mother, we are very speedy, we have&nbsp;
to bring down, put down my speedometer”. You see.

00:46:38.080 --> 00:46:43.520
And this is what we people do not&nbsp;
realize, that we are lethargic here.

00:46:44.640 --> 00:46:48.080
The difference is, lethargic&nbsp;
people they never realize

00:46:48.080 --> 00:46:53.600
because they don’t even have so much strength&nbsp;
to think of that, that we are lethargic.

00:46:55.280 --> 00:47:00.720
My husband’s place, Lucknow, is known&nbsp;
for all kinds of lethargic people.

00:47:01.840 --> 00:47:05.120
So, they had a competition.

00:47:05.920 --> 00:47:10.880
They got all of them in a row&nbsp;
and said, “Whosoever is the most&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:47:12.240 --> 00:47:15.680
lethargic, the laziest, walk one step forward”.

00:47:16.480 --> 00:47:19.200
So everybody walks one step forward.

00:47:19.200 --> 00:47:24.240
But one was from England. He stayed back.

00:47:24.240 --> 00:47:27.280
So the people asked him, “Why&nbsp;
didn’t you step forward?”

00:47:27.280 --> 00:47:28.981
He said, “I don’t even want to do that”.

00:47:28.981 --> 00:47:29.008
[Laughter]

00:47:29.008 --> 00:47:41.440
It’s true that was the laziest.

00:47:41.440 --> 00:47:44.160
So that should not do the case. All right?

00:47:49.440 --> 00:47:53.760
See the working is on still, the&nbsp;
right side, right side, right side.

00:47:53.760 --> 00:47:59.520
It’s all working, yes, yes, yes,&nbsp;
yes, it’s going on all the time.

00:48:00.440 --> 00:48:05.840
Ah! It’s working. Poor things.

00:48:06.960 --> 00:48:09.600
I have seen my grandchildren also. Aradhana,

00:48:09.600 --> 00:48:12.080
she was hardly three years or so,&nbsp;
we had taken her to the airport.

00:48:12.080 --> 00:48:15.120
She said, “No, no”, like that. She&nbsp;
was going on like that, you see.

00:48:15.120 --> 00:48:18.400
So, Kalpana could not understand&nbsp;
why she was so crazy, so fast.

00:48:18.400 --> 00:48:19.840
[To other Sahaja Yogis] Hello, hello, hello!

00:48:20.720 --> 00:48:25.280
Here comes then another mister&nbsp;
[a baby boy]. Is he sleeping?

00:48:25.280 --> 00:48:25.680
Sahaja Yogini: No, no. [Unclear] Kamala

00:48:25.680 --> 00:48:32.800
Shri Mataji: Come along. Where will you sit new?

00:48:32.800 --> 00:48:33.280
Sit here.

00:48:36.400 --> 00:48:41.600
How are you now? Better? All right, I’ll see.

00:48:41.600 --> 00:48:47.840
Ah! This one has come. This one,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:48:56.880 --> 00:49:31.280
see. Just see&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:49:31.280 --> 00:49:32.640
this one.

00:49:32.640 --> 00:49:32.880
May God bless you.

00:49:32.880 --> 00:49:43.840
He’s all right. Poor&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:49:59.200 --> 00:49:59.340
thing.

